    ingredients: [i('Lobster tails',2,'ct'),i('Cavatappi or elbow pasta',1,'lb'),i('Gruyère shredded',1.5,'cup'),i('Sharp cheddar shredded',1,'cup'),i('Parmesan',0.5,'cup'),i('Whole milk',2.5,'cup'),i('Heavy cream',0.5,'cup'),i('Butter',5,'tbsp'),i('All-purpose flour',3,'tbsp'),i('Dijon mustard',1,'tsp'),i('Old Bay seasoning',1,'tsp'),i('Panko breadcrumbs',0.75,'cup'),i('Lemon',1,'ct')],
    recipe: `1. Poach lobster tails 6 min. Cool, remove meat, rough chop.\n2. Cook pasta al dente.\n3. Make béchamel: melt butter, whisk in flour, cook 2 min. Gradually add milk and cream.\n4. Off heat, add cheeses, mustard, and Old Bay. Season.\n5. Fold in pasta and lobster.\n6. Transfer to a baking dish. Top with panko mixed with 1 tbsp melted butter.\n7. Bake at 375°F for 20–25 min until golden and bubbling.\n8. Finish with squeeze of lemon.`,
