    recipe: `1. Slice garlic head in half crosswise, drizzle with oil, wrap in foil. Roast at 400°F for 45 min until golden and sweet. Squeeze out cloves.\n2. Drain and rinse chickpeas. Save the liquid.\n3. Blend chickpeas until a paste forms. Add roasted garlic, tahini, lemon juice, and cumin.\n4. Add ice water while blending — the cold creates a creamier texture. Blend 3 min.\n5. Toast pine nuts. Spread hummus in a dish, make a well, fill with olive oil.\n6. Top with paprika, za\'atar, pine nuts, and parsley.`,
