    recipe: `1. Make chimichurri: finely chop parsley, oregano, garlic, chili, and shallot. Mix with vinegar and olive oil. Season.\n2. Cut cauliflower heads into 1-inch thick steaks through the center, keeping florets attached.\n3. Brush with olive oil, season with paprika, cumin, salt, and pepper.\n4. Sear in a cast iron pan over high heat 3–4 min per side until golden.\n5. Transfer to oven at 400°F for 10 min.\n6. Serve topped with chimichurri and blistered cherry tomatoes.`,
